<subSubSection id="7DBEC7E9FFF7AC03BBEF56CCFCB7FDE6" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="351B9462FFF7AC03BBEF56CCFCB7FDE6" blockId="3.[140,1108,448,1003]" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis id="07D04870FFF7AC03BBEF56CCFE89FE78" bold="true" box="[140,259,448,474]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" reason="1">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="F2A4EFE1FFF7AC03BA7756CDFEE7FE78" authorityName="Masner" authorityYear="1958" box="[276,365,449,474]" class="Insecta" family="Scelionidae" genus="Nixonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="07D04870FFF7AC03BA7756CDFEE7FE78" box="[276,365,449,474]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">Nixonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is superficially similar to 
<taxonomicName id="F2A4EFE1FFF7AC03B9F456CCFCB6FE78" authority="Latreille" authorityName="Latreille" box="[663,828,448,474]" class="Insecta" family="Scelionidae" genus="Scelio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="07D04870FFF7AC03B9F456CCFD5EFE78" box="[663,724,448,474]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">Scelio</emphasis>
Latreille
</taxonomicName>
, and to the larger, more elongate species of 
<taxonomicName id="F2A4EFE1FFF7AC03BA3D56EFFDD0FE5F" authority="Westwood" authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1835" box="[350,602,483,509]" class="Insecta" family="Scelionidae" genus="Macroteleia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="07D04870FFF7AC03BA3D56EFFE57FE5F" box="[350,477,483,509]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">Macroteleia</emphasis>
Westwood
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F2A4EFE1FFF7AC03B9EC56EFFCC9FE5F" authority="Kieffer." authorityName="Kieffer." box="[655,835,483,509]" class="Insecta" family="Scelionidae" genus="Triteleia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="07D04870FFF7AC03B9EC56EFFD60FE5F" box="[655,746,483,509]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">Triteleia</emphasis>
Kieffer.
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="F2A4EFE1FFF7AC03B82456E8FC2AFE5F" authorityName="Masner" authorityYear="1958" box="[839,928,484,509]" class="Insecta" family="Scelionidae" genus="Nixonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="07D04870FFF7AC03B82456E8FC2AFE5F" box="[839,928,484,509]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">Nixonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished by the 14segmented, nonclavate antennae; the strong medial propodeal tooth; and the presence of two tibial spurs on both the mid-and hind tibiae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7DBEC7E9FFF7AC03BBDA5541FD01FD56" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="351B9462FFF7AC03BBDA5541FD01FD56" blockId="3.[140,1108,448,1003]" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis id="07D04870FFF7AC03BBDA5541FEDAFDC5" bold="true" box="[185,336,589,615]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" reason="1">Distribution</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="F2A4EFE1FFF7AC03BA3D5542FE3DFDC5" authorityName="Masner" authorityYear="1958" box="[350,439,590,615]" class="Insecta" family="Scelionidae" genus="Nixonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="07D04870FFF7AC03BA3D5542FE3DFDC5" box="[350,439,590,615]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">Nixonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species richness is centered in southern Africa, but distribution extends north to 
<collectingCountry id="4DB3D4F2FFF7AC03BAE5557DFE46FD29" box="[390,460,625,651]" name="Egypt" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">Egypt</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="4DB3D4F2FFF7AC03BABB557DFDA9FD29" box="[472,547,625,651]" name="Kenya" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">Kenya</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="4DB3D4F2FFF7AC03B94D557CFD01FD28" box="[558,651,624,650]" name="Somalia" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">Somalia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="4DB3D4F2FFF7AC03B9F4557CFD7CFD28" box="[663,758,624,650]" name="Rwanda" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">Rwanda</collectingCountry>
, and the 
<collectingCountry id="4DB3D4F2FFF7AC03B802557CFF7DFD0C" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">Democratic Republic of Congo</collectingCountry>
(former 
<collectingCountry id="4DB3D4F2FFF7AC03BA3F559FFE16FD0C" box="[348,412,659,686]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">Zaire</collectingCountry>
). A single species, 
<taxonomicName id="F2A4EFE1FFF7AC03B90F5598FD75FD0F" authorityName="Johnson &amp; Masner" authorityYear="2006" box="[620,767,659,685]" class="Insecta" family="Scelionidae" genus="Nixonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="krombeini">
<emphasis id="07D04870FFF7AC03B90F5598FD75FD0F" box="[620,767,659,685]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">N. krombeini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is found in 
<collectingCountry id="4DB3D4F2FFF7AC03B8F3559FFC75FD0F" box="[912,1023,659,685]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
, northern 
<collectingCountry id="4DB3D4F2FFF7AC03BBDA55BBFF7DFD73" box="[185,247,695,721]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">India</collectingCountry>
, and southeast Asia (Th ailand, 
<collectingCountry id="4DB3D4F2FFF7AC03B93E55BBFD1EFD73" box="[605,660,695,721]" name="Laos" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">Laos</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="4DB3D4F2FFF7AC03B9B055BBFCB1FD70" box="[723,827,695,722]" name="Vietnam" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
). See http://hol.osu.edu/ map-large.html?id=523 for distribution map.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7DBEC7E9FFF7AC03BBDA55F1FEBDFC49" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="351B9462FFF7AC03BBDA55F1FEBDFC49" blockId="3.[140,1108,448,1003]" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis id="07D04870FFF7AC03BBDA55F1FE92FCB5" bold="true" box="[185,280,765,791]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" reason="1">Biology</emphasis>
. Only one species has been reared: 
<taxonomicName id="F2A4EFE1FFF7AC03B9AF55F2FC17FCB5" authorityName="Johnson &amp; Masner" authorityYear="2006" box="[716,925,765,791]" class="Insecta" family="Scelionidae" genus="Nixonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="watshami">
<emphasis id="07D04870FFF7AC03B9AF55F2FC17FCB5" box="[716,925,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">Nixonia watshami</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a parasitoid of the eggs of 
<taxonomicName id="F2A4EFE1FFF7AC03BA7B542DFDE0FC99" authority="(Walker, 1869)" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[280,618,800,827]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Acanthoplus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="discoidalis">
<emphasis id="07D04870FFF7AC03BA7B542DFE27FC98" box="[280,429,800,827]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">A. discoidalis</emphasis>
(Walker, 1869)
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="F2A4EFE1FFF7AC03B91E542CFC8CFC98" box="[637,774,800,826]" class="Insecta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Orthoptera</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="F2A4EFE1FFF7AC03B870542CFC25FC98" authorityName="Krauss" authorityYear="1902" box="[787,943,800,826]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Tettigoniidae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="F2A4EFE1FFF7AC03B8DC542CFBC2FC99" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1878" box="[959,1096,800,827]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Hetrodinae">Hetrodinae</taxonomicName>
). The subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="F2A4EFE1FFF7AC03BA5E544FFE4BFCFF" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1878" box="[317,449,835,861]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Hetrodinae">Hetrodinae</taxonomicName>
is endemic to Africa and adjacent areas of the Arabian Peninsula (Otte et al. 2009) and all 14 genera are likely to play hosts for 
<taxonomicName id="F2A4EFE1FFF7AC03B89A546BFBDEFC22" authorityName="Masner" authorityYear="1958" box="[1017,1108,871,896]" class="Insecta" family="Scelionidae" genus="Nixonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="07D04870FFF7AC03B89A546BFBDEFC22" box="[1017,1108,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">Nixonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species. Th e host, however, of at least 
<taxonomicName id="F2A4EFE1FFF7AC03B92B5487FD6BFC06" authorityName="Johnson &amp; Masner" authorityYear="2006" box="[584,737,906,932]" class="Insecta" family="Scelionidae" genus="Nixonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="krombeini">
<emphasis id="07D04870FFF7AC03B92B5487FD6BFC06" box="[584,737,906,932]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="34">N. krombeini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which occurs outside the range of Heterodinae in tropical Asia must be some other large orthopteran (
<bibRefCitation id="5135E993FFF7AC03B8DC54A1FEA1FC49" author="Johnson NF &amp; Masner L" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" pagination="1 - 32" refId="ref6133" refString="Johnson NF, Masner L (2006) Revision of world species of the genus Nixonia Masner (Hymenoptera: Platygastroidea, Scelionidae). American Museum Novitates 3518: 1 - 32." type="journal article" year="2006">Johnson and Masner 2006</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
